# Greg CRM — MVP Implementation Plan

A local-first, agent-native CRM where contacts are markdown files and an AI agent does the relationship work. Built for developer-founders who hate Salesforce.

## Architecture Decisions

### Tech Stack
| Layer | Choice | Why |
|-------|--------|-----|
| **Runtime** | Electron | Desktop app, full filesystem access, proven (Obsidian uses it) |
| **Frontend** | React + Vite | Fast dev, HMR, you already know it |
| **Styling** | Vanilla CSS with CSS variables | Dev-tool aesthetic, dark theme, full control |
| **Markdown** | `gray-matter` (frontmatter) + `react-markdown` (render) | Parse YAML frontmatter + render body |
| **File watching** | `chokidar` | Watch contact directory for external changes |
| **Command palette** | Custom `cmdk`-inspired component | Cmd+K is the primary interface |
| **Icons** | `lucide-react` | Clean, dev-tool-friendly icons |

### Contact File Format
Each contact is a [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) file in `~/greg-contacts/` (configurable):

```markdown
---
name: John Doe
email: john@example.com
company: Acme Corp
role: CTO
tags: [investor, technical]
phone: "+1-555-0123"
linkedin: https://linkedin.com/in/johndoe
last_contacted: 2026-03-01
created: 2026-02-15
---

## Notes
Met at YC Demo Day. Interested in our Series A.

## Log
- **2026-03-01** — Sent follow-up email about partnership
- **2026-02-20** — Coffee meeting, discussed roadmap
- **2026-02-15** — Initial intro via Sarah
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The file **is** the database. No SQLite, no JSON store. This means contacts are git-trackable, grep-able, and work offline by default.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Initialization

#### [NEW] Project scaffold at `/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gregg-crm/`

Initialize with Vite + React template, then add Electron via `electron` + `electron-builder`. Key config files:

- `package.json` — scripts for dev (renderer + electron), build
- `vite.config.js` — Vite config for the renderer process
- `electron/main.js` — Electron main process (window, file system, IPC)
- `electron/preload.js` — Secure bridge between main and renderer

---

### Design System

#### [NEW] `src/index.css`

Dark-mode-first design system with CSS variables. Inspired by Linear/Cursor aesthetics:
- Color tokens (dark backgrounds, muted text, accent colors)
- Typography (Inter/JetBrains Mono)
- Spacing scale, border radius, shadows
- Glassmorphism panels, smooth transitions

---

### App Shell

#### [NEW] `src/App.jsx`

Main layout: sidebar (contact list) + main content area (contact detail or welcome screen). Hosts the Cmd+K overlay.

#### [NEW] `src/components/Sidebar.jsx`

Contact list with:
- Search/filter bar at top
- Grouped contact list (alphabetical or by tag)
- Active state highlighting
- "New Contact" button

#### [NEW] `src/components/ContactDetail.jsx`

Selected contact view:
- Header with name, company, role
- Tag pills
- Rendered markdown body (notes + log)
- Inline edit mode (toggle between view and edit)
- Quick actions bar (email, log activity)

#### [NEW] `src/components/CommandPalette.jsx`

Cmd+K overlay:
- Fuzzy search across contacts and commands
- Commands: "New contact", "Search contacts", "Add tag", "Log activity"
- Keyboard-navigable (arrow keys + enter)
- Animated open/close

#### [NEW] `src/components/ContactEditor.jsx`

Markdown editor for creating/editing contacts:
- Frontmatter fields as a clean form
- Markdown body as a textarea
- Live preview toggle

---

### File System Layer

#### [NEW] `src/lib/fileSystem.js`

Core file operations (called via Electron IPC):
- `listContacts()` — read directory, parse all [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) files
- `readContact(filename)` — parse frontmatter + body
- `writeContact(filename, data)` — serialize frontmatter + body, write to disk
- `deleteContact(filename)` — remove file
- `watchContacts(callback)` — chokidar file watcher

#### [NEW] `src/lib/markdown.js`

Markdown utilities:
- `parseContact(content)` — gray-matter parse
- `serializeContact(frontmatter, body)` — gray-matter stringify
- `generateFilename(name)` — slugify name to filename

#### [NEW] `electron/ipc.js`

IPC handlers for the main process:
- File read/write/delete/list handlers
- Directory selection dialog
- File watcher setup

---

### State Management

#### [NEW] `src/hooks/useContacts.js`

React hook for contact state:
- Load contacts from disk on mount
- Real-time updates via file watcher
- CRUD operations that write to disk + update React state

#### [NEW] `src/hooks/useCommandPalette.js`

Hook for command palette logic:
- Open/close state
- Fuzzy search filtering
- Command registry

---

### Sample Data

#### [NEW] `sample-contacts/`

3-4 sample [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) contact files to ship with the app for first-run experience.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

Since this is an Electron app with file system operations, the primary verification is functional:

```bash
# Build check — ensures the app compiles without errors
cd /Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gregg-crm
npm run build
```

### Manual Verification (via browser subagent)

1. **App launches** — Run `npm run dev`, open in browser (renderer process)
2. **Contact list renders** — Sample contacts appear in sidebar  
3. **Contact detail view** — Click a contact, see rendered markdown
4. **Create contact** — Use Cmd+K → "New Contact", fill form, verify [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) file appears on disk
5. **Edit contact** — Toggle edit mode, modify, save, verify file changes
6. **Cmd+K works** — Press Cmd+K, fuzzy search contacts, execute commands
7. **Files are plain markdown** — Open contact files in any text editor, confirm they're valid markdown with YAML frontmatter

> [!NOTE]
> For this MVP, we'll run the React app in dev mode via Vite (browser). The Electron shell will be scaffolded but the **priority is getting the UI and file operations working**. Electron packaging can happen in a follow-up phase. The file system operations will be mocked with localStorage for the browser-based MVP, with the real filesystem layer ready for Electron.
